Power Management IC (PMIC)

Session popupval
Session textval
Session Titefor popup
Show default content
Design Flexibility
Wide input voltage range,
digital interface
& built-in ADC
Programming Flexibility
One-time programmable (OTP)
& multiple-time
programmable (MTP)
Simplifies Design
Maximum integration
in a small package

MPS’ PMIC and multi-output product family include integrated Buck, Boost, Buck/Boost, Efuse, load switch, and Linear regulators. Our PMIC solutions support applications with 3.3V, 5V, and 12V, and higher voltages. Utilizing a monolithic approach, many IC blocks and functions are integrated to support many rails in a system, such as those with FPGAs, Infotainment, SSDs, Access Points, DSL, Set-top boxes, DIMMs, and Whitegoods.

MPS PMICs make it easy to manage multiple power rails with integrated system power sequencing and digital programming capabilities via I2C interface and PmBUS as well as OTP/MTP memory. During development, systems requirements may change, and therefore with starter development/evaluation kits (EVKT/PKTs) from MPS, customers can easily use MPS products to evaluate, make changes to programming, and finalize specs in a timely manner. Our PMICs also support multi-phase (parallel) capability to allow design scalability and minimize the number of BOM components.
